</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/136389517-marmor"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1623763052i/136389517._UY100_CR38,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/136389517-marmor">MarMor</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    It is for the most part. Gary did fly for the French Army of Liberation, his mother did die in 1941, he was a diplomat after the war. Some things are <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    It is for the most part. Gary did fly for the French Army of Liberation, his mother did die in 1941, he was a diplomat after the war. Some things are "literary invention" though - for example, he learned of his mother's death right away in 1941, not 3 years later after all the setup described in the book. I'd say that broadly the stories are true, but embellished. A true literary memoir.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

