        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2306503583" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13339473563883142262">This is the kind of writing I haven&apos;t found (yet) in modern writing. It&apos;s, gosh, how do I put it. Beautiful. For lack of better words, it was beautiful. Full of elegant maxims that is warm and sad.<br/><br/>The very way of weaving emotions into words that is Romain Gary&apos;s could make me blush when Romuschka was put to shame. All the entangling mix of adoration and annoyance, confusion and desire to please, and desperation to get away yet can never really—all too relatable and I&apos;m glad somebody has a way to</span>
  <span id="freeText13339473563883142262" style="display:none">This is the kind of writing I haven't found (yet) in modern writing. It's, gosh, how do I put it. Beautiful. For lack of better words, it was beautiful. Full of elegant maxims that is warm and sad.<br /><br />The very way of weaving emotions into words that is Romain Gary's could make me blush when Romuschka was put to shame. All the entangling mix of adoration and annoyance, confusion and desire to please, and desperation to get away yet can never really—all too relatable and I'm glad somebody has a way to beautifully express the sometimes-grotesque mess that is the relationship of mother and child. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13339473563883142262" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

