<span id="freeTextContainer1446664172927283076">Quite an entertaining, interesting read. It had quite a nice writing style and some nice ideas.<br/><br/>HOWEVER, personally, I was too irritated by characters. First of all, yes, the mother sacrificed a lot and loved the child. However, what others call a great love, i would say is quite conditional and limited love - i love you only because you will some day become someone important and fulfill my needs to be someone important. And if you will not, i will be mad and angry at you and you will not be wort</span>
  <span id="freeText1446664172927283076" style="display:none">Quite an entertaining, interesting read. It had quite a nice writing style and some nice ideas.<br /><br />HOWEVER, personally, I was too irritated by characters. First of all, yes, the mother sacrificed a lot and loved the child. However, what others call a great love, i would say is quite conditional and limited love - i love you only because you will some day become someone important and fulfill my needs to be someone important. And if you will not, i will be mad and angry at you and you will not be worthy of my love.<br /><br />Second, the main character was annoying with his fake humility and humble brags and with his general grandiose, egocentric writing about his amazing ideals and humanism in the past and the present. Do i need to mention his disgust with "fags", writing with satisfaction how someone that insulted him later was shot, wishing that some ladies that insulted his mother were not able to escape communist regime, him deciding to take a 16 year old girl from the african tribe, not speaking any common language to be his lover (but she had very soft face and beautiful skin, so its understandable)?</span>
  <a data-text-id="1446664172927283076" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
