<div id="review_3176437694" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3176437694" />
    <a title="Nhi Doãn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/56337874-nhi-do-n"><img alt="Nhi Doãn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641622805p2/56337874.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3176437694?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nhi Doãn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nhi Doãn" href="/user/show/56337874-nhi-do-n">Nhi Doãn</a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780241347638" href="/book/show/38470209-promise-at-dawn">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3176437694" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15545815052706491530">I have read Promise at Dawn twice and can recall its opening paragraph quite easily: “It is over. The beach at Big Sur is empty and cool and the gentle sand is kind to the fallen…” Never have I encountered a man, a narrator more tender and noble in his endeavors. Romain lived, indeed, an extraordinary life, in striving to protect the naive, grandiose nursery tale in the heart and mind of an old woman - his dear and endearing mother; to give form and meaning to her life of struggles and sacrifice</span>
  <span id="freeText15545815052706491530" style="display:none">I have read Promise at Dawn twice and can recall its opening paragraph quite easily: “It is over. The beach at Big Sur is empty and cool and the gentle sand is kind to the fallen…” Never have I encountered a man, a narrator more tender and noble in his endeavors. Romain lived, indeed, an extraordinary life, in striving to protect the naive, grandiose nursery tale in the heart and mind of an old woman - his dear and endearing mother; to give form and meaning to her life of struggles and sacrifices with marvelous triumphs. He had been loved, so much, and that love stayed with him to the very last day: “the umbilical cord had continued to function.” What a shame, then, that he chose to end his life by a bullet. Though he denied it, I wonder if he was truly ever happy after his mother’s death.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15545815052706491530" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


