    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1317458453" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1317458453" />
    <a title="Vic Van" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15874338-vic-van"><img alt="Vic Van" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1569926355p2/15874338.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1317458453?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vic Van" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vic Van" href="/user/show/15874338-vic-van">Vic Van</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782070363735" href="/book/show/24917316-la-promesse-de-l-aube">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1317458453" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13723732013752194463">I came to reading this book, having found it listed in &apos;Dans les forêts du Sibérie&apos; among the books Sylvain Tesson had taken with him and because one of the first French novels that I ever read and loved, was &apos;La vie devant soi&apos;. Another reason why I felt that this book might appeal to me, was because it deals extensively with the influence of motherly love on a person&apos;s life and independence in life.<br/><br/>The book is a humorous account of the life of Romain Gary, from his early childhood years as a r</span>
  <span id="freeText13723732013752194463" style="display:none">I came to reading this book, having found it listed in 'Dans les forêts du Sibérie' among the books Sylvain Tesson had taken with him and because one of the first French novels that I ever read and loved, was 'La vie devant soi'. Another reason why I felt that this book might appeal to me, was because it deals extensively with the influence of motherly love on a person's life and independence in life.<br /><br />The book is a humorous account of the life of Romain Gary, from his early childhood years as a refugee from Communist Russia to his days as an army pilot during The Second World War. You learn how his mother had great expectations for him from the very beginning and how he puts every possible effort into either trying to fulfil those expectations or into saving his mother the grief of having to learn of his failures.<br /><br />Another important theme is both protagonists' unconditional love for their adoptive France.<br /><br />I loved the humour. I loved the atmosphere. I loved the story.<br /><br />It's hard to imagine this man committing suicide later in his life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13723732013752194463" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

