<span id="freeTextContainer14963262020599628003">Once I&apos;ve stumbled into an interview of some very authoritative and famous person, where he told that no one ever tought him what it means to be a Man. Neither surroundings, nor media. But it was THIS book where he did find out the answer. Quite promising, right?<br/>Only one word. Touching. Extremely touching. <br/>I dare say men use to be nakedly sincere mainly either telling about their love affairs, or business successes and failures. But such issues as responsibility, fears, inner growing up, relatio</span>
  <span id="freeText14963262020599628003" style="display:none">Once I've stumbled into an interview of some very authoritative and famous person, where he told that no one ever tought him what it means to be a Man. Neither surroundings, nor media. But it was THIS book where he did find out the answer. Quite promising, right?<br />Only one word. Touching. Extremely touching. <br />I dare say men use to be nakedly sincere mainly either telling about their love affairs, or business successes and failures. But such issues as responsibility, fears, inner growing up, relations with mother, from early childhood throught years, in all it's bareness and complexity, deliciously flavoured with irony and wonderful style, - is definitely a rare find. And definitely must read. For women - as a precious peep at a man's inside, for men - look paragraph 1 of a review ;)</span>
